   Notes on Opinion Format and Multiple Opinions
     __________________________________________________________________

   Please select from the following menu to find opinions by date of
   issue:
   Month: [January__] Year: [2002_] Go!
   (*) All Opinions ( ) By Day ( ) Release Sheets

   Important Notes:
     * The opinions are an ASCII/text version of the original formatted
       opinion.  This ASCII/text version does not include the entire range
       of formatting (layout, fonts, italics, bold, underline, etc.) that
       is normally part of the printed paper version.

     * The letter following the docket number indicates that subsequent
       opinions or orders have issued. For example 98-1001A designates the
       initial opinion in a case and 98-1001B designates a subsequent
       opinion and/or amending order in the same case. Any amended opinion
       and the corresponding amending order will usually appear on the
       same day and will be identified by successive letters.

     * WordPerfect versions of the opinions are available from the:

     * Court's ABBS bulletin board system.
     * Edward Bennett Williams Law Library at the Georgetown University
       Law Center - a searchable site containing all of the Court's
       published opinions since March, 1995 in both WordPerfect and Word
       formats.
